Humidity.Description: Humidity affects the perceived temperature. Higher humidity can make the temperature feel hotter.
Humidity and dew point are closely related. Higher humidity increases the likelihood of dew formation.
Humidity can affect air quality by influencing the concentration of pollutants and allergens in the air.
High humidity levels promote the growth of mold, which can have negative effects on indoor air quality and health.
